I worked at Taymour and I would have to say it was the worst experience that I ever had teaching and getting along with my co-workers. I was treated with racism, decisions were made behind my back without me being able to speak up for myself. When I tried to speak up for myself the director would yell in my face and dismiss me. My co-workers would push their work on me and we're often lazy and took credit for my labor while blaming issues on me. I was not treated well at all. Although the school loves recruiting non Egyptian teachers, I would not accept a job at this school because if you do you will be treated with racism from the top down regardless of how good of a job you do.
